<br>
euthanise the stupid and mean! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utoreyj01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>toreyj01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/11/02 7:09:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1879.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://us.f1.yahoofs.com/users/da3bf501/bc/My+Photo+Album/is_ani_e0.gif?bcVvmU9AKuak95UR WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you own a lead pipe...</span><hr size=1> Okies some nice chap comes here to find help in taking care of an obviously nice little dog who was injured.  This was not some lipoma that needs removal or a toenail clipping, this was out of the ordinary.<br>
<br>
So you are not a dog lover, wonderful.<br>
<br>
There are those of us who give to causes, and the reason we do is because it touches our hearts.  I have a three legged dog named Tripod (believe it or not) who was rescued in the middle of some woods dying of heartworm and starvation.  Four months and a thousand dollars later the rescue put him up for adoption and I drove 200 miles to get him.<br>
<br>
This dog is my best friend.<br>
<br>
